net.openhft.chronicle.engine.api.tree

Interface AssetTree

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    VanillaAssetTree

    public interface AssetTree
extends net.openhft.chronicle.core.io.Closeable
    A Hierarchical collection of Assets in a tree structure.

        Parameters:

      • registerSubscriber

        default <E> void registerSubscriber(@NotNull
                                    String uri,
                                    Class<E> eClass,
                                    Subscriber<E> subscriber)
                             throws AssetNotFoundException
        Register a subscriber to a URI with an expected type of message by class.

        e.g. if you subscribe to a type of String.class you get the keys which changed, if you subscribe to MapEvent.class you get all the changes to the map.
        Parameters:
        uri - of the asset to subscribe to.
        eClass - the type of event/message to subscribe to
        subscriber - to notify which this type of message is sent.
        Throws:
        AssetNotFoundException - the view could not be constructed.
